pair cost put forward.
Our specification calls for the rear wheel to be replaced, not refurbished.=
 The vehicle sustained a light to moderate collision impact directly to the=
 wheel. Mercedes-Benz's Position Statement on Wheel Repair and Reconditioni=
ng is explicit that no reconditioning process, including heating, straighte=
ning, welding, material removal, reshaping or replating, is an approved rep=
air method, and that a reconditioned wheel does not meet production specifi=
cation. On that basis, balancing and refinishing a wheel that has taken a d=
irect impact does not meet the manufacturer's position.
Our rate reflects the appropriate rate for a vehicle of this marque. Our sp=
ecification also includes ADAS identification and pre- and post-repair diag=
nostic checks, which require an appropriately equipped and trained facility=
 rather than a general bodyshop or wheel refurbishment company.

The driver-reported vibration and juddering is consistent with a wheel affe=
cted by collision impact. This would not necessarily appear on a routine MO=
T inspection unless the vehicle were examined with the wheel removed, and c=
ontinued use of the vehicle does not of itself establish roadworthiness. We=
 did suggest that a temporary repair may be a viable option in this case ho=
wever we have not been made aware if this has not been carried out.

We confirm that we have no financial interest in the settlement of this cla=
im and see no reason to deviate from our repair specification.

Any further queries, please let us know.

